The '''United States Senate election of 1888''' was an election which, coinciding with [[Benjamin Harrison]]'s [[United States presidential election, 1888|victory]] over incumbent President Grover Cleveland, had the [[Republican Party (United States)| Republican Party]] gain twelve seats in the [[United States Senate]], mostly from newly-admitted States.

As this election was prior to ratification of the [[Seventeenth Amendment to the United States Constitution|seventeenth amendment]], Senators were chosen by [[State legislature (United States)|State legislatures]].

== Results ==
[[51st United States Congress|51st Congress]] (1889â1891) 

* Majority Party: Republican (51)
* Minority Party: Democratic (37)
* Other Parties: (0)
* '''Total Seats: 88'''

